history.content: Hey I'm not too sure about 61c and 186, but I'm currently in 126 and 170, which I would imagine is comparable, and it is definitely manageable. I heard that 61c can be a major time suck, so I'd be wary of that.

children.subject: I'd say hard and work intensive but not absurdly so.
I do, but I thought it was just a recommendation? I checked some threads on Piazza, and people said it was mainly fine to take 186 without 61c knowledge. Is that not the case?

Unless the prereq is enforced, you'll be ok. There is very little overlap between 61C and 186 besides a short stint in caching and possibly some other topics like disks. (Disclaimer: I have not taken the web based version so perhaps material has changed recently)
Just checking that you know 61C is a prereq for 186

IDK about EE126 but CS 186 and CS 61c is a tough schedule already.

61C has so much work. Weekly labs(they take longer than 2 hours), 3 HW assignments on Edx(2-5 hours, assuming you're not stuck), 2 coding HW assignments(10-20 hours), 3 projects(broken up into two parts, so basically 6 projects, you have 1 week to complete each).

186 has 5 HW assignments, you have two weeks to complete each. Also have 2 midterms. These two can be tough when hws are assigned the same time. For example, I have 186 project due next Wed, CS 61c proj due next mon, 186 midterm next thurs, and another 61c proj assigned next monday. Oh, and each week I have 61c lab.

This schedule is certainly doable, although you may want to take 186 a lighter semester.

history.content:
Hi, I'm a junior student, planning to take EE126, CS61C, and CS186 next semester. 

I want to get into ML, have to take my last lower div, and heard that 186 is considered very useful for software engineering, which is why I decided upon this schedule. 

What is your opinion on the toughness of each of these classes, and the schedule overall. Is it a little too tough? (I am not the best with time management) Would you recommend I drop one for now, and, if so, which one?

Previously, I have taken 61A/B, 16 A/B, 70, 170, 188, C100 in terms of EE/CS courses.

Thanks for the help!
